zchunk
------------------------------------------
zchunk is a compressed file format that splits the file into independent
chunks. This allows you to only download changed chunks when downloading a new
version of the file, and also makes zchunk files efficient over rsync.

Runtime requirements:
  cygwin-3.0.7-1
  libargp-20110921-3
  libcurl4-7.66.0-1
  libssl-devel-1.1.1d-1
  libssl1.1-1.1.1d-1
  libzck-devel-1.1.4-1bl1
  libzck1-1.1.4-1bl1
  libzstd-devel-1.4.3-1
  libzstd1-1.4.3-1
  pkg-config-1.6.0-1

Build requirements:
(besides corresponding -devel packages)
  binutils-2.29-1
  cygport-0.33.1-1
  gcc-core-7.4.0-1
  meson-0.51.2-1
  ninja-1.9.0-1

Canonical website:
  https://github.com/zchunk/zchunk

Canonical download:
  https://github.com/zchunk/zchunk/archive/1.1.4.tar.gz

-------------------------------------------

Build instructions:
  1. unpack zchunk-1.1.4-X-src.tar.xz
  2. if you use setup to install this src package,
     it will be unpacked under /usr/src automatically
        % cd /usr/src
        % cygport ./zchunk-1.1.4-X.cygport all

This will create:
  /usr/src/zchunk-1.1.4-X-src.tar.xz
  /usr/src/zchunk-1.1.4-X.tar.xz
  /usr/src/libzck1-1.1.4-X.tar.xz
  /usr/src/libzck-devel-1.1.4-X.tar.xz

-------------------------------------------

Files included in the binary package:

(zchunk)
  /usr/bin/unzck.exe
  /usr/bin/zck.exe
  /usr/bin/zck_delta_size.exe
  /usr/bin/zck_gen_zdict.exe
  /usr/bin/zck_read_header.exe
  /usr/bin/zckdl.exe
  /usr/share/doc/Cygwin/zchunk.README
  /usr/share/doc/zchunk/DOCKER_TESTING.md
  /usr/share/doc/zchunk/LICENSE
  /usr/share/doc/zchunk/README.md
  /usr/share/doc/zchunk/zchunk_format.txt

(libzck1)
  /usr/bin/cygzck-1.dll

(libzck-devel)
  /usr/include/zck.h
  /usr/lib/libzck.dll.a
  /usr/lib/pkgconfig/zck.pc

